**Switch_Configuration:**
Any Login_Credentials_Configuration -> User will be the Name of the Branch/HQ & Password will always be Cisco
Ex: user: Branch_1 Pass: Cisco 

1. Basic Switch Configuration
Hostname configuration
Enable secret password
Disable IP domain lookup
Banner message 
############################################
        Only Authorized Employees
############################################

2. Management Plane Security
Create a management VLAN ( VLAN 100 )
Configure the management IP address
Set default gateway
Configure SSH access
Create local user accounts 
Set SSH version 2 only
Configure session timeouts

3. Access Control
Configure console port security
Configure AUX port (disable if unused)
Configure VTY lines for SSH only
Set access-class restrictions
Configure privilege levels

4. Port Security
Enable port security on access ports
Set the maximum MAC addresses to 2 per port
Configure violation actions (shutdown/restrict)
Configure sticky MAC addresses
Enable port security aging

5. VLAN Security
Create VLANs ( IT -> 10 / Sales -> 20)
Assign access ports to specific VLANs
Configure trunk ports with specific VLANs
Set native VLAN (VLAN 99 )
Enable VLAN pruning

6. Trunk Security
Configure trunk negotiation (ON desirable)
Specify allowed VLANs on trunks
Set native VLAN different from data VLANs
Enable DTP protection

7. STP Security
Enable PortFast on End-User devices
Enable Root Guard
Enable BPDU Guard on access ports
Set STP priority if required

8. DHCP Security
Enable DHCP Snooping
Configure trusted ports (uplinks)
Configure untrusted ports (access ports)

9. ARP Security
Enable Dynamic ARP Inspection (DAI)
Configure DAI on VLANs
Set ARP validation
Configure trusted ports for DAI

10. IP Source Guard
Enable IP Source Guard
Configure on access ports
Set binding table sources
